{"posts":[{"no":121623803,"now":"04\/17\/17(Mon)22:28:27","name":"Anonymous","sub":"Moldilocks could face Assault With a Deadly Weapon","com":"California&#039;s Assault with a Deadly Weapon (&quot;ADW&quot;) statute is California Penal Code 245(a)(1). The code reads as follows:<br><span class=\"quote\">&gt;Any person who commits an assault upon the person of another with a deadly weapon or instrument other than a firearm shall be punished by imprisonment in the state prison for two, three, or four years, or in a county jail for not exceeding one year, or by a fine not exceeding ten thousand dollars ($10,000), or by both the fine and imprisonment<\/span><br><br><br>The California courts have declared on numerous occasions that a bottle can constitute a deadly weapon for the purpose of the statute.<br><span class=\"quote\">&gt;*See e.g.*, *People v. Brown (2012),* 210 Cal.App.4th 1, 6-7 (&quot;For example, *a bottle or a pencil*, while not deadly per se, may be a deadly weapon within the meaning of section 245, subdivision (a)(1), when used in a manner capable of producing and likely to produce great bodily injury.&quot;) <\/span><br><span class=\"quote\">&gt; *See also* *People v. Zermeno (1999)*, 21 Cal.4th 927, 931, 89 Cal.Rptr.2d 863, 986 P.2d 196 (finding that a beer bottle is a deadly weapon)<\/span>","filename":"download","ext":".jpg","w":520,"h":779,"tn_w":166,"tn_h":250,"tim":1492482507865,"time":1492482507,"md5":"y4kA7AxBO6rh43SO+xwrcQ==","fsize":57954,"resto":0,"id":"0myP7aaw","country":"US","bumplimit":0,"imagelimit":0,"semantic_url":"moldilocks-could-face-assault-with-a-deadly","country_name":"United States","replies":0,"images":0,"unique_ips":1}]}